description.narrative: To strengthen the design of effective public policies on health, UNICEF promoted capacity building activities to 1.161 municipalities through the SEAL strategy on different themes, including SRHR. Public advocacy efforts (campaigns and social mobilization) increased the knowledge of the population on the importance of improved regulations on food labeling, including a strategy for the promotion of healthy feeding habits to obesity prevention. Lastly, UNICEF contributed with the expanding of HIV testing and linkage to treatment of youth and adolescents in the risk age group through the Youth Aware strategy in 09 large urban centers. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:06/02/2020
